    {
      "content": "2. Subscriptions and accounts",
      "pos": [
        7788,
        7817
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In order to work with Azure, you need one or more Azure subscriptions.",
      "pos": [
        7819,
        7889
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Resources, like cloud services or virtual machines, exist in the context of those subscriptions.",
      "pos": [
        7890,
        7986
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Enterprise customers typically have an Enterprise Enrollment, which is the top-most resource in the hierarchy, and is associated to one or more accounts.",
      "pos": [
        7990,
        8143
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For consumers and customers without an Enterprise Enrollment, the top-most resource is the account.",
      "pos": [
        8146,
        8245
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Subscriptions are associated to accounts, and there can be one or more subscriptions per account.",
      "pos": [
        8248,
        8345
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure records billing information at the subscription level.",
      "pos": [
        8346,
        8406
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Due to the limit of two hierarchy levels on the Account/Subscription relationship, it is important to align the naming convention of accounts and subscriptions to the billing needs.",
      "pos": [
        8408,
        8589
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For instance, if a global company uses Azure, they might choose to have one account per region, and have subscriptions managed at the region level.",
      "pos": [
        8590,
        8737
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For instance, you might use this structure.",
      "pos": [
        8830,
        8873
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Following the same example, if a region decides to have more than one subscription associated to a particular group, then the naming convention should incorporate a way to encode the extra on either the account or the subscription name.",
      "pos": [
        8966,
        9202
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This organization allows massaging billing data to generate the new levels of hierarchy during billing reports.",
      "pos": [
        9203,
        9314
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The organization could look like this.",
      "pos": [
        9407,
        9445
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Microsoft provides detailed billing via a downloadable file for a single account or for all accounts in an enterprise agreement.",
      "pos": [
        9538,
        9666
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can process this file, for example, by using Microsoft Excel.",
      "pos": [
        9667,
        9732
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This process would ingest the data, partition the resources that encode more than one level of the hierarchy into separate columns, and use a pivot table or PowerPivot to provide dynamic reporting capabilities.",
      "pos": [
        9733,
        9943
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Implementation guidelines recap for subscriptions and accounts",
      "pos": [
        9949,
        10011
      ]
    },
    {
